# Shipwright Command Center — example .env file.
#
# Copy to `.env.local` and uncomment / edit one block below to control
# how the dev servers (Vite on :5173, Hono on :3847) bind. Both halves
# read the same .env.local — Vite via dotenv at config-load time, Hono
# via lib/env at boot.

# ============================================================================
# Network bind profile (ADR-08X)
# ============================================================================
#
# SHIPWRIGHT_NETWORK_PROFILE picks one of three pre-set bind modes for both
# servers in one place. Lowercase only; UPPER / MixedCase rejected so a typo
# never silently falls through to a less-safe default.
#
#   local     - both servers bind to 127.0.0.1 only.
#               Safe everywhere (cafe, hotel, public Wi-Fi).
#               Default if SHIPWRIGHT_NETWORK_PROFILE is unset.
#
#   tailscale - both servers bind to your Tailscale IPv4 address only.
#               Reachable from your other Tailscale-paired devices via
#               the authenticated, encrypted Tailscale mesh; invisible
#               to everyone else (cafe Wi-Fi, hotel LAN, etc).
#               Local access from this machine via the Tailscale-IP
#               (e.g. http://100.105.29.88:5173/) — `localhost` will
#               NOT work (intentional; one address everywhere).
#
#   open      - both servers bind to 0.0.0.0 (all network interfaces).
#               *** ONLY use on trusted networks (home / office). ***
#               On startup, both halves print a deutliche WARNING.
#
# Tailscale-IP resolution (only relevant for `tailscale`):
#   1. SHIPWRIGHT_TAILSCALE_IP env var (this file) wins if set.
#   2. Else `tailscale ip -4` subprocess (first valid IPv4 line).
#   3. Else loud-fail with actionable error message.
#
# Backward compat: explicit VITE_HOST / HONO_HOST env vars still work
# and override the profile. If you set them, the profile is ignored
# for that half.
# ============================================================================

# === LOCAL (default — safe everywhere) ===
#SHIPWRIGHT_NETWORK_PROFILE=local

# === TAILSCALE (recommended for mobile / cafe / hotel) ===
#SHIPWRIGHT_NETWORK_PROFILE=tailscale
# Optional override (auto-detected via `tailscale ip -4` if unset):
#SHIPWRIGHT_TAILSCALE_IP=100.105.29.88

# === OPEN (only on trusted networks) ===
#SHIPWRIGHT_NETWORK_PROFILE=open

# ============================================================================
# Low-level overrides (legacy — bypass the profile)
# ============================================================================
# These are the historical opt-in vars. They still work; setting either
# one DEFEATS the profile decision for that half. Use them only if you
# need finer-grained control than `local` / `tailscale` / `open` provide.
#
#VITE_HOST=true             # 0.0.0.0 + allowedHosts:true
#VITE_HOST=100.105.29.88    # bind to a specific interface
#HONO_HOST=true             # `::` (IPv4 + IPv6 dual-stack)
#HONO_HOST=100.105.29.88    # bind to a specific interface

# ============================================================================
# Ports (override only when running parallel worktrees on the same machine)
# ============================================================================
#PORT=3848         # Hono port (default 3847)
#VITE_PORT=5174    # Vite port (default 5173)
